INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'f4bd1645-9b1b-49af-a66a-1763f31c2957',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$axum — Global Error Handling with a Consistent JSON Response Format$escape$,
  $escape$axum doesn't have a single global error handler middleware, but you get the same effect by implementing `IntoResponse` on a custom error type and returning `Result<impl IntoResponse, AppError>` from every handler. Define `AppError` as an enum wrapping domain errors, then implement `IntoResponse` once — serializing a unified `{ "code": "...", "message": "..." }` JSON body with the correct HTTP status. Pair this with a `From<sqlx::Error>` (or other infallible conversions) so the `?` operator propagates errors without boilerplate at the call site. For truly unhandled panics or tower middleware errors, wrap your router with `HandleErrorLayer` from `tower` — axum exposes this via `ServiceBuilder`. This layer catches errors that escape handlers (e.g. timeout, body extraction failures) and lets you map them to the same `AppError` shape. The result: every error path — handler panics, extractor rejections, timeouts — emits a uniform JSON envelope your clients can rely on.$escape$,
  $escape$use axum::{http::StatusCode, response::{IntoResponse, Response}, Json};
use serde_json::json;

pub enum AppError {
    NotFound(String),
    Internal(anyhow::Error),
}

impl IntoResponse for AppError {
    fn into_response(self) -> Response {
        let (status, code, message) = match self {
            AppError::NotFound(msg) => (StatusCode::NOT_FOUND, "NOT_FOUND", msg),
            AppError::Internal(e) => (StatusCode::INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR, "INTERNAL", e.to_string()),
        };
        (status, Json(json!({ "code": code, "message": message }))).into_response()
    }
}

// Handler — ? just works
async fn get_user(Path(id): Path<i64>) -> Result<Json<User>, AppError> {
    db::find_user(id).await.map(Json).map_err(|e| AppError::NotFound(e.to_string()))
}$escape$,
  $escape$rust$escape$,
